<style is:inline>
*{margin:0;padding:0;box-sizing:border-box}
:root{--dl-blue:#7799CC;--dl-dark:#0a0e14;--dl-panel:#111827;--dl-border:#1e293b;--dl-text:#e2e8f0;--dl-muted:#64748b;--dl-accent:#8ab4f8;--dl-green:#22c55e;--mono:'JetBrains Mono',monospace}
body{background:var(--dl-dark);color:var(--dl-text);font-family:var(--mono);font-size:13px;line-height:1.7;min-height:100vh}
a{color:var(--dl-accent);text-decoration:none}
a:hover{text-decoration:underline}
.container{max-width:900px;margin:0 auto;padding:20px 16px}
h1{font-size:22px;font-weight:700;color:var(--dl-text);letter-spacing:-.5px;margin-bottom:4px}
h1 .iata{color:var(--dl-blue)}
h2{font-size:16px;font-weight:700;color:var(--dl-text);margin-bottom:12px;padding-bottom:6px;border-bottom:1px solid var(--dl-border)}
p{margin-bottom:12px}
.header{border-bottom:1px solid var(--dl-border);padding:20px 0 16px;margin-bottom:24px}
.header .nav{font-size:11px;color:var(--dl-muted);margin-bottom:12px}
.header .nav a{color:var(--dl-accent);font-size:11px}
.subtitle{font-size:12px;color:var(--dl-muted)}
.hub-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr;gap:16px;margin-bottom:32px}
.hub-card{background:var(--dl-panel);border:1px solid var(--dl-border);border-radius:8px;padding:20px;transition:border-color .2s}
.hub-card:hover{border-color:var(--dl-blue)}
.hub-card .hub-code{font-size:28px;font-weight:700;color:var(--dl-blue);letter-spacing:1px}
.hub-card .hub-name{font-size:14px;font-weight:600;margin:4px 0 2px}
.hub-card .hub-info{font-size:11px;color:var(--dl-muted);margin-bottom:10px}
.hub-card .hub-link{display:inline-block;background:var(--dl-blue);color:#fff;padding:6px 16px;border-radius:4px;font-size:11px;font-weight:600;text-decoration:none;letter-spacing:.5px}
.hub-card .hub-link:hover{background:#0069c0;text-decoration:none}
.cta-block{background:var(--dl-panel);border:1px solid var(--dl-border);border-radius:8px;padding:20px;text-align:center;margin-bottom:32px}
.cta-block .cta{display:inline-block;background:var(--dl-blue);color:#fff;padding:10px 24px;border-radius:4px;font-size:12px;font-weight:600;text-decoration:none;margin-top:8px}
.cta-block .cta:hover{background:#0069c0;text-decoration:none}
.section{margin-bottom:32px}
.section p{color:var(--dl-text)}
.section ul{padding-left:20px;margin-bottom:12px}
.section li{margin-bottom:6px}
.footer{background:var(--dl-panel);border-top:1px solid var(--dl-border);padding:8px 16px;font-size:9px;color:var(--dl-muted);text-align:center;line-height:1.8;margin-top:40px}
@media(max-width:600px){
  h1{font-size:18px}
  .hub-card .hub-code{font-size:22px}
}
</style>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@300;400;500;600;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
</head>
<body>

<div class="container">

  <!-- Header -->
  <div class="header">
    <div class="nav"><a href="/">&#8592; Widget Watch</a> / Hubs</div>
    <h1>Delta Air Lines <span class="iata">Hub Airports</span> — Live Status & Delays</h1>
    <div class="subtitle">Real-time operations at all 9 Delta hubs · Delays, cancellations, on-time performance</div>
  </div>

  <!-- Intro -->
  <div class="section">
    <p>Delta Air Lines operates a network of <strong>9 hub airports</strong> spanning the United States, Asia, and the Pacific. Together, these hubs handle thousands of daily departures connecting over 350 destinations worldwide. Widget Watch tracks every Delta flight at every hub in real time — updated every 30 seconds.</p>
    <p>Select a hub below to see live delay counts, on-time performance, WiFi fleet information, seasonal delay patterns, terminal details, and more.</p>
  </div>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <div class="cta-block">
    <p style="margin:0">See all hubs on the live dashboard with real-time delay counts and flight positions.</p>
    <a class="cta" href="/">Open Widget Watch Dashboard &#8594;</a>
  </div>

  <!-- Hub Grid -->
  <h2>All 9 Delta Air Lines Hubs</h2>
  <div class="hub-grid">
    {hubOrder.map((key) => {
      const hub = hubSummaries[key];
      return (
        <div class="hub-card">
          <div class="hub-code">{hub.iata}</div>
          <div class="hub-name">{hub.name}</div>
          <div class="hub-info">{hub.subtitle}</div>
          <a class="hub-link" href={`/hubs/${key}`}>View {hub.iata} Hub Status &#8594;</a>
        </div>
      );
    })}
  </div>

  <!-- Content Sections -->
  <div class="section">
    <h2>Delta Air Lines Hub Network</h2>
    <p>Delta's hub-and-spoke network is built around three tiers of hubs:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Major domestic hubs:</strong> <a href="/hubs/ord">Chicago O'Hare (ORD)</a> and <a href="/hubs/den">Denver (DEN)</a> are the two largest, handling over 1,200 daily departures combined. ORD is Delta's global headquarters and largest operation.</li>
      <li><strong>Gateway hubs:</strong> <a href="/hubs/ewr">Newark (EWR)</a> serves as the East Coast transatlantic gateway, <a href="/hubs/sfo">San Francisco (SFO)</a> and <a href="/hubs/lax">Los Angeles (LAX)</a> are Pacific gateways, and <a href="/hubs/iah">Houston (IAH)</a> is the primary Latin America gateway.</li>
      <li><strong>International hubs:</strong> <a href="/hubs/nrt">Tokyo Narita (NRT)</a> is Delta's Asian hub, and <a href="/hubs/gum">Guam (GUM)</a> connects Pacific island routes. <a href="/hubs/iad">Washington Dulles (IAD)</a> serves both domestic and transatlantic routes.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>What Widget Watch Tracks at Each Hub</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Live flight counts</strong> — active Delta flights at each hub, updated every 30 seconds</li>
      <li><strong>Delay monitoring</strong> — real-time delay counts, cancellations, and on-time percentage</li>
      <li><strong>Ground stops & FAA alerts</strong> — NAS status affecting hub operations</li>
      <li><strong>Departure & arrival schedules</strong> — with on-time stats and equipment swap detection</li>
      <li><strong>WiFi fleet</strong> — which aircraft at each hub have satellite internet</li>
      <li><strong>Weather conditions</strong> — METAR observations and NEXRAD radar overlay</li>
      <li><strong>Seasonal delay patterns</strong> — historical context for weather-driven disruptions</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2 id="faq">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <h3>What are Delta Air Lines' hub airports?</h3>
    <p>Delta Air Lines operates 9 hub airports: Chicago O'Hare (ORD), Denver (DEN), Houston Intercontinental (IAH), Newark Liberty (EWR), San Francisco (SFO), Washington Dulles (IAD), Los Angeles (LAX), Tokyo Narita (NRT), and Guam (GUM). ORD is the largest with approximately 750 daily departures.</p>

    <h3>Which Delta Air Lines hub has the most flights?</h3>
    <p>Chicago O'Hare (ORD) is Delta's largest hub with approximately 750 daily departures. Denver (DEN) is the second-largest with about 540. Houston (IAH) and Newark (EWR) each handle around 400 daily departures.</p>

    <h3>How can I check delays at Delta Air Lines hubs?</h3>
    <p>Widget Watch monitors delays, cancellations, and ground stops at all 9 Delta hubs in real time. Visit <a href="/">widgetwatch.org</a> to see the hub health bar with on-time performance, or visit individual hub pages for detailed delay patterns, seasonal trends, and live flight counts.</p>

    <h3>Which Delta hubs have international flights?</h3>
    <p>All 9 Delta hubs have some level of international service. The primary international gateways are: <a href="/hubs/ewr">Newark (EWR)</a> for transatlantic flights, <a href="/hubs/sfo">San Francisco (SFO)</a> for transpacific routes, <a href="/hubs/iah">Houston (IAH)</a> for Latin America, and <a href="/hubs/nrt">Tokyo Narita (NRT)</a> for Asia connections.</p>
  </div>

</div>

<!-- Footer -->
<div class="footer">
  <div><a href="/" style="color:var(--dl-accent);text-decoration:none">Widget Watch</a> · Unofficial · Not affiliated with Delta Air Lines, Inc. · Data may be delayed · <a href="/" style="color:var(--dl-accent);text-decoration:none">Open Dashboard &#8594;</a></div>
  <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:6px 12px;margin-top:4px">
    <span>Data: <a href="https://www.flightradar24.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color:var(--dl-muted);text-decoration:none">FR24</a> · <a href="https://aviationweather.gov" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color:var(--dl-muted);text-decoration:none">AWC</a> · <a href="https://nasstatus.faa.gov" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color:var(--dl-muted);text-decoration:none">FAA</a></span>
    <span style="white-space:nowrap">Built by <a href="https://github.com/notjbg" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color:var(--dl-accent);text-decoration:none">Jonah Berg</a> · <a href="https://x.com/theblueboard" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color:var(--dl-accent);text-decoration:none">Follow @theblueboard</a></span>
  </div>
</div>

</body>
</html>
